// Constructs an empty vector
// - A: The type of elements in the vector
// = An empty vector of type `(Vector A #z{})`

Vector/nil 
: ∀(A: *) 
  (Vector A #z{})
= λA ~λP λnil λcon 
	nil

// The ~ (self-inst) operator is used here to instantiate the self-type of the Vector.
// It allows us to consume the self-type defined in the Vector datatype,
// which is necessary to properly construct and manipulate vectors.
// Without it, we wouldn't be able to access the nil and cons cases of the vector.